        <updateDate>2005-10-07T15:09:53Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Retirement Account Emergency Access Act of 2005 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to exclude from gross income distributions from certain tax-qualified retirement plans to individuals residing in federally-declared disaster areas. Allows such distributions to be recontributed to retirement plans within five years of an initial distribution.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
